social_posts.post_text: You can build anything. Keep going. #everydaypower
Your positive impact is more important than you might be aware of. Keep going. #everydaypower
Double down on you. You’re worth the risk. And as we get older we realize, the biggest risk of all is never having the experience of investing and betting on ourself. Keep going. #everydaypower

The bad news is its been you this whole time. The good news is its been you this whole time. We all have doubts. We all let our doubts stop us at times. It’s all doubt. All doubt can be reduced. All of it. Much respect. Keep going. #everydaypower
Enough words. Set your shoulders, set your face, and set your schedule towards the life and things you want. Keep going. #everydaypower

We’re all setting an example for something. It can be an example of what to do. Or, it can be an example of what not to do. Either way, the end goal, of all the infinite types of leadership, are to bring people to higher ground. Not by our well crafted words, but by our actions. As imperfect as they might be. Much love. Keep going.

We’re programmed to romanticize our younger years. But so much can happen when you have experience, skills and all the confidence that comes with that. Believe in your future. Keep going. #everydaypower
You can navigate the uncertainty. You can handle anything that pops up. You’re worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower

Enjoy your life. Enjoy your journey. Yes, when you want something you don’t currently have, chronic irritability is real. Yes, the frustration of being where you’re at vs. the image you have in your head of where you want to be, that’s real. But all that is energy. That energy doesn’t need to go inward. It can go outward. It can fuel part of your game. Mission, love and your own curiosity can fuel other parts. You got this. Just keep going. #everydaypower
I heard this a million times growing up. Thankful I did. Thanks Dad. Keep going. #everydaypower
Build systems that pull you forward. Destroy systems that hold you back. Pay attention to what you’re doing. Keep going. #everydaypower

When you stick with something, your inner power transforms. It transforms from an idea that sounds good, to an undeniable truth that will impact all areas of your life. Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower

Pursue your vision like your life depends on it, because it does. It’s been proven that having a strong sense of purpose improves the quality of all areas of your life. Make the decision. Try. And keep adjusting. Keep going. #everydaypower

Your future is an investment. Your mindset is an investment. Your courage is an investment. Your vision in an investment. Your resilience is an investment. It’s all an investment. It’s all worth it in the long run. Keep going. #everydaypower

As human, we always find a way to survive and land on our feet. The future is inherently bright. As long as there’s a sun, it will rise. The critics will say, ‘but even the sun burns out.’True, but that’s 5 billion years away. Don’t get too far ahead of yourself. Life continues. You continue. Keep going. You and your goals are worth the effort. #everydaypower

Shoutout to everyone who’s not making the same old excuses and has truly dedicated their time, energy and resources to figuring out a positive way forward. That progress impacts your life and becomes a symbol of what’s possible for those around you. Keep going. #everydaypower
Be both thankful and productive. It’s not one or the other, it’s both. All at the same time. Keep going. #everydaypower

What other questions would you add to the list? Whenever you do an honest self reflection, you tap into the energy that leads to your higher self. Be honest with yourself. That’s where the power and freedom is. Reflect to keep going. #everydaypower
What else would you add to the list? What are some big decisions we’re faced with? What else impacts the quality of your life? Let’s discuss. Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower

Find out all the amazing ways your life changes when you stick to one of your most important goals. One area of your life, can and will positively impact the other areas. It’s all connected. Stay connected to the real you. Stay connected to the best you. Keep going. #everydaypower
Stay active and stay hungry. 💯Keep going. #everydaypower

If you use revenge to “get even”, now you’re off path, chasing ghosts, and burning time you’ll never get back. The best revenge is no revenge. The best revenge is living a great life. That type of revenge pushes you, your family and your circle forward. Keep going. #everydaypower
Spread ❤️❤️❤️❤️ #everydaypower

Surround yourself with people who get it. Surround yourself with people who are also pursuing things. If those people aren’t around you at the moment, don’t worry, you’ll meet them along the way. The people you meet while in pursuit, are also probably in pursuit. Keep going. Sunday thoughts. #everydaypower
Keep learning. Stay excited. You’re worth it. Your future is worth. Let’s get it. Let’s go. Keep going. #everydaypower
Action and progress shatter all excuses in the long run. Keep going. #everydaypower

It will be worth it. You can build just about anything you want if you put the time in and build a team. The time is going to pass regardless, might as well build something exciting, meaningful and impactful. Start where you are. Keep going. #everydaypower

The more you own your gifts, talents and interests; the more consistently you give them to the world. You’re not steady working on your dream because you’re so disciplined. You developed discipline because you knew your dreams were worth it and you knew you had a shot at making it happen. Let’s get it. Keep going. #everydaypower

You are everything all at the same time because you come from everything. You don’t come from a thing, you come from everything. Everything has influenced you and you influence everything. It’s not one or the other. It’s everything at the same time. Don’t trap yourself with simple thinking. You’re complex. Life is complex. And that’s a good thing. Keep going. #everydaypower
You have the time. Never stop learning. Keep going. #everydaypower
Be curious enough to see how much you can develop. Keep going. #everydaypower

Your existence is connected to greatness. Your existence is connected to millions of years of strength. Your existence is connected to every life that came before you. Reflect on that power. Sit in that power. That’s the real you. Everything else is a distraction. Keep going. #everydaypower
You know what matters. You know which way to go. Go that way. Spend your time there. Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower

Trust in everything. Trust in yourself. Trust in others. Trust in the universe. Trust in a higher power. Trust in the process. Trust in good habits. Trust in the pursuit. Trust in your own personal evolution. If you have no trust, build it back by trusting yourself. Build daily. Keep going. #everydaypower

You’re a link in a chain that goes all the way back. Like…all the way back. How far back? Far! You don’t just come from a set of parents or a household. You come from all of it. Everything. There’s power in that framework. Keep going. #everydaypower
Mentally celebrate all the small wins for a moment. Reinforce the beauty of the path. Don’t stop. Keep going. #everydaypower

Be aware of all the things that encourage quitting. Be aware of all the things that sound like they’re helping you, but might not be. Be aware of all the ways we over extend ourselves and our mind and what that really leads to. Keep going. #everydaypower
Rest your body. Rest your mind. Then…return back to your adventure. Keep going. #everydaypower
Monday vibes. Build trust in yourself. Keep your own word to yourself. Build yourself up. Don’t look back. Keep going. #everydaypower
What do you want? How many times are you willing to get back on path? Fair questions. Keep going. #everydaypower
There is no boredom when this your mindset. There is no competing video game or any other form of distraction. Yes, rest counts as a step if what you need is rest. Keep going. #everydaypower

The love and positive energy inside you is infinite. Let it out! No one can take your kindness for weakness if you’re already giving love most of the time anyway. They didn’t take it, you were giving it out already anyway. Happy Valentines Day. Keep going. #everydaypower
Patterns can hold us back or they can turn us into a growth machines. Pay attention. It’s all flexible. It’s all patterns. Keep going. #everydaypower
You’re 10X more flexible than you believe. Keep going. #everydaypower
Happy Friday World!!! Never forget the power you have at all times. Keep going. #everydaypower

When you believe in the work you’re providing, you’re focusing on the people who benefit from your work. The people who benefit from your work are one of your sources of fulfillment and purpose. It’s all about what you’re focused on. Focus can be adjusted when we educate ourselves on other perspectives. Keep going. #everydaypower

Your authentic self is supposed to help guide you forward, not hold you back.
Your authentic self is the version of you that feels most confident, light and free. Keep going. #everydaypower

Your day is your life. How you start your day is how you start your life. Your mornings matter. Your morning routine matters. Make it what you want. Make it the best it can be. Think about it. Work on it. It’s yours. Keep going. #everydaypower

The only thing that can stop you from living is death. Just about everything else can be navigated. Live your life. It’s healthy to remind yourself of your mortality. It helps keep your fears the right and proportionate size. Much love. Happy Friday. Keep going. #everydaypower
Everything can change for you. Keep going. #everydaypower
💯💯💯💯💯💯💯 Keep going. #everydaypower

The average career is 40 years. So if it takes 10 years to become great, that means you have 30 years of playing at a world class level. Work will take up a huge portion of your life. Might as well become great at what you do, and watch how that level of output impacts you, your family and strangers. Keep going. #everydaypower
It’s all one big game. It’s all one big mind game anyway. Every day, every moment is +1 or -1. Keep stacking those moments. Keep going. #everydaypower
When you pay attention to the details of your life and how they come together…you can make anything work. Keep going. #everydaypower

Baby back ribs in the smoker at 325 for about 3 hours. Exercise with some Nas on. Read and play with my daughter. Bonus…call a few friends back this weekend. What could you do? What’s within arms reach right now? Keep going. #everydaypower

We’re all connected at the core. We’re all dealing with demons. Our demons don’t make us an island, our demons are what we all have in common. They connect us. All demons are defeated over time if we just confront them. Confront them. Keep going. #everydaypower

Reflecting as I approach my 38th lap around the sun. Life is a true ride and the adventure is in that we really don’t know what’s coming next. And we don’t need to. We just need to know two things: whatever happens I can navigate it and I can make almost anything happen. Both are true, at the same exact time. Thankful for platforms like these, where I can express myself on topics I find important. Thank you everyone for tuning in over the years. I’m not stopping anytime soon. I got a bunch more decades to go. Love y’all. Keep going. #everydaypower

Perfectionism is just a fancy excuse. Don’t worry about looking bad, not as many people are examining you as you might think. Most people are too focused on their day to day life. You’re free. Keep going. #everydaypower

You have enough time. You can create time. You can make time. Learning is always time well spent. The more you learn about something, the more capable you feel. The more capable you feel, the more your dedication and motivation snowball. Keep learning. Keep experimenting. Keep going. #everydaypower

The seeds of greatness you sow today will blossom into a more prosperous world for all. Your accomplishments can inspire your family, strengthen your community, bring hope to strangers, bolster the economy, and enrich the fabric of society. The magnitude of your impact may be difficult to quantify, but the ripples you create can transform countless lives in ways you could never imagine.

Remember, your journey towards greatness isn't just about you; it's about the countless lives you can change along the way. Embrace the pursuit of excellence, knowing that your passion and dedication will have a lasting impact on the world.

It's all worth it. You're worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower

Friday thoughts! You gotta know what you want. Then go that way, even if you’re unsure. You’ll be unsure on all levels. That’s normal. All you gotta know for sure is, it’s worth it, you can do it and most importantly…you’re worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower

Every day can be +1, -1, or 0. Every day we can move forward, in general or in a specific area. Every day we can move backwards, in general or in a specific area. Every day we can have no movement, in general or in a specific area. It’s all movement or lack thereof. And anything that involves movement is a cycle. And all cycles are games that repeat. Every day is another chance to get better. And that chance is what makes being alive a blessing. Keep going. #everydaypower
Stick with it. You’re worth it. Your future is worth it. Happy Sunday. Keep going. #everydaypower

You’re worth the time and effort. Don’t listen to anybody who tries to tell you to just accept it. Life’s too short to be stuck with the same exact problem for decades. Get to work. There’s no more important project than you. Then, watch everything else fall into place. One positive improvement in your life always impacts another area. Much love. Monday grind time. Keep going. #everydaypower

Long term thinking is a skill. And like any other skill it can be developed. Your life is the most important project you’ll ever work on. Learn all the skills you can. And don’t stop. Keep going. #everydaypower
Repeat after me: “I’m not afraid of the amount of time it will take. The time will pass faster than I can imagine and then I’m there.” Start and keep going. #everydaypower
The bottom line is, you’re worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower

Pick your path. There is no easy road. Aiming low isn’t easy, it’s very hard to live like that. Aiming high isn’t easy, either. It’s all work. It’s all endless work. Every single day. But one path is more exciting than the other. One path makes a bigger impact, for a longer amount of time, than the other. One path provides more meaning and purpose than the other. It’s always a choice. Every day can be a fresh one. Every day can build on the last one. Select your path. You’re worth it. Your future is worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower

Your ability to focus is a skill that can develop and get better. All things and anything can get better with practice, which is one of the true beauties of life. One of the best ways to make real progress in your life is to aim at what YOU ACTUALLY WANT. Not what looks good and sounds good, but aiming at the life and lifestyle you actually want. Who do you want to be? What kind of helpful activities do you find fun? How do you want your days to be? How do you want to earn a living? What vision do you have for the family you create? (If you want to, of course) How do you want to feel most of the time? How do you want your mental and physical health to be? We can come up with good and simple questions all day long, you get the idea. Discipline becomes so much easier when you’re pursuing something you truly want. Be honest with yourself. Keep going. #everydaypower
You know this already. But many things are worth repeating. This is one of them. Keep going. #everydaypower
Give yourself another chance. And, another. And, another. And, another. Forever. Keep learning. Failure is normal. Tons of  failure is part of the journey. Keep going. #everydaypower
The game is played inside. You know this. Keep going. #everydaypower

What you consume you become. On all levels. No area of life is off limits from this rule. Surround yourself with people, experiences and information that support your evolution on all levels. You’re worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower
Time goes fast. Fast AF. Use that to your advantage. If you can start, you can continue. Keep going. #everydaypower
You’re worth infinite attempts. Happy Friday. Keep going. #everydaypower
Monday thoughts. This week, trust yourself a little bit more than you did last week. It’s scary for everybody. But it’s more than worth it. Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower

Everything is created. Even peace. Peace can’t be all the time, that’s impossible. But those moments of peace are key for your clarity, decision making and tapping into your higher self. Your worth the time investment. Keep going. #everydaypower
You know what to do. Stop talking yourself out of it. Keep going. #everydaypower
You’re worth a million attempts. But most people quit before they even try, or they quit after 2-3 attempts. Give yourself more of a chance than that. Keep going. #everydaypower
There’s a special type of power you possess when you know what you have. Tap into that energy every day. Give thanks daily. Grow from where you’re at. Keep going. #everydaypower

Good intentions pave the way, but it's our actions that truly make a difference. Let's not just dream of a better world, but actively work towards it. Embrace the power of positive change by turning those noble thoughts into tangible results. Remember, every small step counts in building a brighter future for all. Dare to be the catalyst that transforms good intentions into meaningful progress, proving that the heart of change lies in the actions we take. So, rise up and conquer the world with your deeds, for actions will always speak louder than intentions. #everydaypower
Every thing that stays alive, evolves. So if you want your drive to stay alive, make sure your motivations are evolving along with you. Keep going. #everydaypower
If you can start, you can continue. Keep going. #everydaypower

The better you get at directing your time and attention, the better everything gets. A scattered mind can’t be a happy mind. A focused mind is a happy mind because it means you’re present. And when you’re present, you’re giving your time and attention to the moment. And all things grow from the moment. All living things are here to grow. Keep going. Happy Friday. #everydaypower

In the movie of your life, you personally know the director, the producer, the set, the crew, the characters and how it starts. But how does it end? What happens in the middle? All of it is up to you. And that’s both scary and exciting, but not equally, it can be way more exciting. Turn your progress into a game. If you have time to watch random content, or even critically acclaimed content, you have time to pay attention to your own story. You can adjust the script at any time. Keep going. You’ll never regret it. #everydaypower
Your work and life will speak for itself. Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower

Step into your power and own your journey. There's a profound strength in being misunderstood and yet having no desire to justify, explain, or manage others' perceptions. Your time and energy are precious commodities, too valuable to spend on anything but living your most fulfilling life.

Consider each moment of misunderstanding as an opportunity. It's your chance to rechannel your energy towards your true purpose, nourishing the joy and wellbeing of you and your family.

Enjoy the peace that comes with letting that type of control go. It's not about controlling how others see you, it's about honoring your authenticity. When you invest in yourself and those you love, you're paving the way for a life of passion, purpose, and deep satisfaction.

Take that bold step today. March forward with resilience, celebrate your true self, and direct your energy where it truly matters. Keep going. #everydaypower

It’s all you. And that’s a good thing. Because what we do is part of the 0.00000001% of things we can control. There’s trillions of things buzzing and moving around, all around us, every moment…and we have zero control over all of it. But yet, we’re still here. Alive. Active. Outside. Moving. With life. With opportunity. With love. With fight. With power. There’s so much power in that 0.000001% that we can control. It’s wild when you take a moment to pause and think about it. Focus on what you can control and what you can control expands. You’ll never regret focusing on what you can control. Focus brings happiness and progress. Keep going. #everydaypower

No one knows what they're doing. That's the secret. 

From the greatest minds to the everyday person, we're all navigating the maze of life, figuring it out as we go. 

Embrace this truth and dare to still dream and think big. Since we’re all figuring it out as we go, it’s important to see every day as a chance to learn, apply and grow. 

And when doubts creep in, remember that perseverance is just another choice we can make. 

Stick with it. That’s where the information is. 

Keep pushing forward, and let your determination lead you to new levels of life. 

There's no telling what you can achieve. Keep going. #everydaypower

💥 Many days won't match the grand visions in your mind, and that's okay. Progress and productivity can change day to day, with big swings. All good. All normal. But the problem is…we over react. When I learned to  master those tough days without self-criticism or surrender, I knew I could stay in the game forever. 🚀

In this game of life, staying in the game is EVERYTHING. 👊🏼 So, don't give up! Keep pushing forward, no matter how small the steps may seem. Remember, every tiny stride counts, and each setback is an opportunity to learn and grow. 🌱

You've got what it takes to overcome obstacles and rise above challenges. Believe in yourself and trust the process. Perseverance and resilience are the building blocks of triumph. Keep going, keep striving, and keep pursuing your most exciting goals. Your persistence will create miracles. ✨ #StayInTheGame #KeepGoing #everydaypower

🚀 In the journey of adulthood, I've discovered that the choices we make when boredom strikes play a significant role in shaping our lives. 🌟

Success, happiness, inner peace, gratitude, productivity, and even our sleep and eating habits are all influenced by how we respond to those moments of restlessness. It's easy to overreact and engage in activities that move us backward.

But here’s the truth: Boredom is OK. It’s a natural part of life. And knowing it’s just boredom, can help us to not take these impulses so seriously. 💪🏾

Instead of succumbing to the urge to escape boredom with mindless distractions, let’s embrace it as an opportunity. Here are a few practical tips:
1️⃣ Reflect: Use boredom to pause, reflect, and reconnect with your goals and values. It's a perfect time for introspection and self-discovery.
2️⃣ Learn: Engage in activities that expand your knowledge and skills. Read, listen to podcasts, or take up a new hobby. Invest in personal growth.
3️⃣ Create: Channel your creativity and explore new ideas. Write, draw, or pursue any artistic endeavor that brings you joy and fulfillment.

Remember, your choices during boredom can propel you forward or set you back. Embrace the discomfort, stay focused on your path, and keep going. You, your journey, and your future are all worth it! 💫💛#everydaypower #EmbraceBoredom #KeepGoing

You’re a force of nature and your destiny is progress. Your destiny is forward motion. It doesn’t always feel that way, but it is. Admitting you have power can be scary, but it’s worth the fear. Never forget the power you have and strength you come from. Everything living is connected to everything else that’s alive. Everything that’s alive is connected to all life from the beginning of time. Let that sink in. Then, keep going. #everydaypower

There is power in writing.

There is power in writing in down and feeling that surge of excitement as you look at it.

There is power in your words.

It’s not just a pipe dream.

What excites you about life is real.

Other people don’t need to see it, only you do.

Write down what you want and look at it.

You know. You’re not confused.

Go that way.

Keep going. #everydaypower

I have little patience for excuses, and I can be demanding. But I also know that I'm a great leader, and I create a positive and supportive work environment. I'm always looking for ways to help my team grow and develop both in and outside of work.

If you're an entrepreneur, I encourage you to ask yourself these same questions. It's important to be honest with yourself, and to be willing to make changes if necessary. Your team is your most valuable asset, so it's worth the investment to make sure you're creating a great place to work.

Keep going. #everydaypower

You can do difficult things. You can do boring things. You can do things that suck. Don’t focus on how you feel before. We all feel the same way before…like not doing it and just chillen. Focus on how you’ll feel after. Proud. Thankful. And on the way! Keep going. #everydaypower

But don’t just be aware. Be aware so you can take accurate action. You can do things you’ve never done before. Stick with it. Keep going. #everydaypower

And now, things become a game. Which makes the overall experience of pursuit, more fun and exciting. It becomes a game of how many attempts can you get in per day, per week, per month. A game of how many reps can you get in per day, per week, per month, per year. It becomes more fun because you know it’s just a matter of time. And you know your greatness is 100 percent in your hands. When you realize that, it’s over! When you realize that, the real you can begin! Keep going. #everydaypower

What you consume you become. On all levels. No area of life is off limits from this rule. Surround yourself with people, experiences and information that support your evolution on all levels. You’re worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower
You know this already. But many things are worth repeating. This is one of them. Keep going. #everydaypower

Pick your path. There is no easy road. Aiming low isn’t easy, it’s very hard to live like that. Aiming high isn’t easy, either. It’s all work. It’s all endless work. Every single day. But one path is more exciting than the other. One path makes a bigger impact, for a longer amount of time, than the other. One path provides more meaning and purpose than the other. It’s always a choice. Every day can be a fresh one. Every day can build on the last one. Select your path. You’re worth it. Your future is worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower

Long term thinking is a skill. And like any other skill it can be developed. Your life is the most important project you’ll ever work on. Learn all the skills you can. And don’t stop. Keep going. #everydaypower

Friday thoughts! You gotta know what you want. Then go that way, even if you’re unsure. You’ll be unsure on all levels. That’s normal. All you gotta know for sure is, it’s worth it, you can do it and most importantly…you’re worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower

The average career is 40 years. So if it takes 10 years to become great, that means you have 30 years of playing at a world class level. Work will take up a huge portion of your life. Might as well become great at what you do, and watch how that level of output impacts you, your family and strangers. Keep going. #everydaypower
What else would you add to the list? What are some big decisions we’re faced with? What else impacts the quality of your life? Let’s discuss. Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower

You don’t need to be “young”, you need to be excited and interested. There’s a future version of you, within yourself, just waiting to come out. This future version of you is hoping you don’t quit, just because your goals didn’t show up how you would like by 18 or 25. Don’t get caught up in the hype. The young superstars make the headlines, as they should, because doing awesome things while you’re super young is rare. And some industries, like sports of course, favor the “young”. But outside of a few industries, age is your advantage! But we’ve been trained to think, if it doesn’t happen when you’re “young”, it won’t happen for you. That’s backwards. If all your major life goals happened when you were 18-25, you might not be able to handle it, manage it and keep it. But with time, when it happens, you’ll know how to nourish it and really make the most of it. Time is always on your side when you’re learning, applying and adjusting. Much respect. Keep going. #everydaypower

What are 10 things you can do, that are within arms reach, that would push what you’re working on forward? Don’t get tricked into the hamster wheel. You’re capable of hoping off. You’re capable of building on the side. Keep building. Keep being productive. Keep going. #everydaypower
Build systems that pull you forward. Destroy systems that hold you back. Pay attention to what you’re doing. Keep going. #everydaypower

We’re programmed to romanticize our younger years. But so much can happen when you have experience, skills and all the confidence that comes with that. Believe in your future. Keep going. #everydaypower
Feelings of anxiety in an area get a little weaker every time you complete something in that area. Keep going. #everydaypower

What’s the best way to get revenge on your haters? Do nothing at all. Who cares. Focus your energy on what you find important. You’ll become so focused and excited by your progress and opportunities that your haters are not even on your mental radar. Keep going. #everydaypower

Your future is worth infinite attempts. Your future health is worth infinite attempts. Your family’s future is worth infinite attempts. Your career’s future is worth infinite attempts. Your connection to a higher power is worth infinite attempts. You’re worth all of it. Keep building. Keep going. #everydaypower
You grow when you HAVE TO. Put yourself in a position where you have to. Keep going. #everydaypower
Talking yourself out of it is a habit, not the truth. Keep going. #everydaypower
Starting small gives you the space and time to become great. It’s a blessing, not a problem. Get started. Keep going. 💯🙏🏾 #everydaypower
Your growth is worth your time and energy, and so are your best ideas. Stay excited. Stay dedicated. Keep going. #everydaypower
Know what works for you. Keep going. #everydaypower
It literally pays to pay attention. Keep going. #everydaypower

Time can be on your side. Get started. Time only works against you when you delay. Take a moment, and think back to where you were three years ago. What about five years ago? What about 10 years ago? It’s a blur, right? It’s wild how when we look back on time, we think how fast it was. But, when we look forward in time, it feels slow and so far away. The past reminds us how fast time is. The future tricks us into thinking time is slow and painful. The next couple of years will become a blur just like the past couple of years. The next couple of years will happen just as fast as the past couple of years. Might as well spend that time building. Get started and put time back on your side. Keep going. #everydaypower
You’re all of it. You’re connected to everything and everything is connected to you. Your energy is endless. Keep going. #everydaypower

Goals are scary, that’s why we go with the flow. Disappointment hurts, that’s why we try to avoid it. And accountability sounds like way too much pressure to live a free and happy life…but that’s all a game. It’s all a maze that’s easy to get trapped in. A meaningful goal can be the exact excuse you’ve been looking for to rise above your old ways. A goal that you really believe is worth it, can only be reached by addressing ALL of you. Your biggest and most exciting goals can’t be reached with only the good parts of you, with only the parts of you you’re comfortable with. It’s gotta be all of you. ALL of you has gotta rise. And you will. If you pursue what you want. Much respect. Keep going. #everydaypower

Have you forgotten all that you’ve overcome? Do you remember the times you were at the crossroads and you made the right move? What about when you made the wrong move, then was set back, then had to figure that out. Do you remember? Or is buried? Buried underneath years and years of the day to day grind. Just because you haven’t thought about it in a while, doesn’t mean it didn’t happen. You can still learn and relearn from it now. You’ve never been totally stopped…ever. Your existence is proof of that. Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower

Give yourself a fresh start. Whenever you need it. You’re never really starting from scratch. You’re always building. You’ve been building this whole time. When you were consistent, you were building. When you were inconsistent, you were building, you were just building something else. Forgive yourself. Forgive yourself to move forward. Forgiving yourself acknowledges all the things that you wish you did different in the past. It allows you to put it to rest. Putting it to rest, redirects your energy from the past, to the present and future. You can move forward. You can tap into almighty progress. You’re worth every attempt. Don’t just try harder, try better. You’re worth infinite attempts. Get back up. Keep going. #everydaypower

The worst morning routines are ones that keep you in bed and are random. You’re starting the day powerless! Create a routine that works for you. These are examples and ideas of routines that include some fundamentals to help you get your head and body ready for the day. Who’s willing to try this one? Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower

Talk to yourself like believing in yourself is your job. Talk to yourself like you know you’ll figure it out. Talk to yourself and question yourself. Talk to yourself like you know it’s possible. Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower
Your future self is excited and curious to see what you do with the moment. The moment is yours. You can make progress any way that works for you. Keep going. #everydaypower

So many things to be thankful for. The irony is, it’s equally easy to take all those same things for granted. It takes effort to remind ourselves of these things. It’s work. It’s daily work. It’s work worth doing. You’re worth the work. Keep going. #everydaypower
It’s You vs. You. And when you put it like that, you’re always worth the attempt. You’re always worth the effort. We're all wired to pursue.  We're all wired for progress. Keep going. #everydaypower
You can become who you want to be. Period. Keep going. #everydaypower
When you make the process the goal, you bring the dream from the future to the present. Keep going. #everydaypower
Create the time and space to turn your daily learnings into your everyday genius. You got this. Document your journey. It will be the best book you’ve ever read. Keep going. #everydaypower

The sun comes after the darkness. Always. The sun is natural. The darkness is too. Visit the darkness sometimes. There’s freedom there. There’s power there. There’s desire there. There’s clarity there. Don’t be afraid of the darkness. You won’t get lost in it. But it will remind you what’s really at stake here. The darkness can be very powerful in getting you started and in keeping you going. Keep going. #everydaypower

You are your best investment. You are the dream asset. You are the stock that you got in early. You are the crypto that you got in early. You are the determining factor in your life transcending. Everything seems shiny when the light hits it. But you glow. When you invest in yourself, you glow. You shine in the light, but you also glow in the dark. Every time you invest in yourself, you invest in your own ability to generate light. Every time you invest in yourself you develop your ability to generate the life you want. Don’t get tricked. Don’t get fooled. The best investment will be in yourself, and then all the things that your self is pursuing. Much respect. Keep going. #everydaypower
Flip the script. Make your challenges afraid of YOU. Keep going. #everydaypower

Living with regret and resentment is always more difficult than the progress you’re trying to make. The difference is, the pain of figuring it out is right now and the pain of regret might be 5, 10 or 15 years away. When the pain is that far away, we underestimate it. When the pain of figuring it out is so close, we overestimate it. Pursue the life you want. That’s you’re adventure. Get started. Keep going. #everydaypower
We all have insecurities. That’s not a problem. That’s part of your journey. Keep going. #everydaypower
Our identity is way more flexible than we think. Keep going. You're worth infinite attempts. Keep going. #everydaypower

Don’t spend anytime trying to measure how “real” or “fake” people are. That’s the wrong type of math. When you value being real, it’s easy to get stuck on other people’s ways. But at the end of the day, all those measurements don’t add up to any real progress. It’s just another distraction. Keep going. #everydaypower
There’s no show more interesting than the life you’re creating. Every. Single. Day. Let’s get it. Keep going. #everydaypower
A credible source is 100 more valuable than a viral cliche. Keep going. #everydaypower
We’ve all had this day or will have this day. Keep going. #everydaypower
When your higher self talks to you…listen. Keep going. #everydaypower

Honor your ability to be flexible and adapt to anything. You’re designed to adjust, adapt and be who you need to be. Don’t ever get tricked into thinking you’re permanently stuck, mentally or physically. Keep going. #everydaypower
The work you put in for yourself gets positively spilled over into others. And vice versa. Keep going. #everydaypower
It’s worth it. And most importantly, you’re worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower

The toughest conversations are the ones you have with yourself. If you can have those convos, it all gets easier from there. But the more you avoid the conversations with yourself, the more you avoid everything. Keep going. #everydaypower
The universe is always expanding and so are you. Keep a positive attitude and you’ll recognize all the opportunity around you and right in front of you. Keep going. #everydaypower
A huge percentage of our problems and stress come from overreacting to things that will pass in 3,6 or 12 months. Keep your eyes on the prize. Keep going. #everydaypower
A little direction goes a looooooooong way. Keep going. #everydaypower

Life can feel like it’s moving so fast. For example, this week we could’ve done 148 helpful things, but donated all our attention to the 4 things that annoyed us. All normal. Keep building. Keep going. #everydaypower

Aiming to be perfect will eventually exhaust you to the point of quitting. Aiming to be a little bit better turns every day into a game that you didn’t have to buy at a store or download to your phone. Aiming to be a little better each day, will be more engaging and entertaining than any series you can stream. I had to repost this 3 times due to all the typos. So i did. Much love. Keep going. #everydaypower

social_posts.post_text: You can change. But only if you really think you have to. Keep going. #everydaypower
It’s wild to think we can become great at holding our own selves back. Keep going. You’re worth infinite attempts. #everydaypower
We build every day. What a blessing. Keep going. #everydaypower
The more thankful you are, the stronger you are. The stronger you are, the more you can move how you want. Keep going. #everydaypower
You’re competing against who you were yesterday, last month, last year and last decade. Keep going. #everydaypower
Let the games begin!!!! How do you get to the next level? I have no clue, I just keep playing and the answers reveal themselves. Keep going. Keep going. #everydaypower

You know who can give you permission??? Take a good long look in the mirror!!! That’s where the power is!! Start small. Grow bigger. And never lose excitement for what you can give, do, be and experience. Let’s get it. Keep going. #everydaypower

Ambition and curiosity will lead you down the pathway of solving your own problems. Which then puts you in perfect position to help others do the same. You’re worth infinite attempts. Keep going. #everydaypower
We just don’t believe it. But what if we did? What would be different? It’s worth it. You’re worth it. Keep going. #everydaypower
No one wants to do it. But we know we gotta do it. Keep going. #everydaypower

When you have success, you have haters, it comes with it. But if you’re still in the brainstorming phase, those aren’t haters holding you down, those are your own doubts. Either way, none of it has to stop you. Either way, the pursuit of a goal will force you to develop real ways to deal with criticism, doubt, rejection and fear. It’s all worth it. You’re worth it. You’re worth infinite attempts. Keep going. #everydaypower
Get around a group of people who identity as learners, doers, thinkers, and those excited about the future. Keep going. #everydaypower

Any new habit or lifestyle change can become second nature, if you can make it past the shitty phase that feels like work. You’re worth it. It’ll all make sense in the long run. Keep going. #everydaypower
It’s been You Vs You this whole time. Stay excited. Keep going. #everydaypower

You knew the details. You felt the fear. You could’ve quit and been justified. But you thought long term. You thought about how worth it, it was. And you just kept going. Be proud of you. #everydaypower
When you have it on the inside, you can recognize it on the outside. When you see it on the outside, the pursuit begins. Keep going.

Don’t let the smaller parts of you stop the biggest parts of you. Don’t focus on your fear and insecurity so much, that you forget about all the amazing strengths, talents and blessings you have inside of you and around you. See all of it. Then focus on the parts that feed you. Keep going. #everydaypower
A lot of these feelings of anxiety come from not knowing where you’re going. Know where you’re going. Keep going. #everydaypower
Study your struggles and your problems become pathways that elevate multiple areas of your life. Keep going. #everydaypower
What else would you add to the list? Keep going. #everydaypower
What might happen if you don’t stop? Keep going. #everydaypower
One way to let go of bad habits is to focus your attention on developing the good ones. You’re worth infinite attempts. Keep going. #everydaypower

You’re not as bored as you think you are. You’re not as stuck as you think you are. You’re not as unclear as you think you are. You might just be used to filling up every moment with junk activities. Take a break from the junk, and be stunned with how quick you get clear. Keep going. #everydaypower
You’re way more flexible than you think. Keep going. #everydaypower

Everyone’s schedule is different. But what we all have in common is our ability to grow and develop. Growth only stops when you’re dead. Everything else is full of life. Keep growing. Keep going. #everydaypower
If this speaks to you it’s most likely because you’re on your way to the next level. It rings true cause you’re living that life. Stay locked in. Stay excited. Keep going. #everydaypower
Don’t forget to take care of yourself! Keep going. #everydaypower
The pursuit is complicated enough. Don’t make it any more complicated than it needs to be. Keep going. #everydaypower
Thankful to all the parents out there who keep moving forward. Your example is the best show your kids will ever watch. Much respect. Keep going. #everydaypower
It’s all making you stronger, smarter and more aware. Much love and respect. Keep going. #everydaypower #thankful
Count your blessings. Recognize your blessings. On a regular basis. Keep going. #everydaypower
My Dad always told me, “No one can make you do it, and no one can stop you from doing it.” I’m thankful he told me that over and over and over. Keep going. #everydaypower
When you know who you want to be, how you want to live, and what you want to provide; the energy and clarity is endless. Much respect. Keep going. #everydaypower

It’s wild to think that what we do when we’re not working or grinding has just as much to do as the work its self. Let go of anything that’s been weighing you down. The further you want to go, the lighter you need to be. Keep going. #everydaypower

Paradox’s are a real part of the human journey. It doesn’t mean you’re being contradictory. It doesn’t mean you’re being inconsistent. It means you’re moving with the rhythm and ebbs and flows of your life. As long as you’re paying attention to how things are really working in your particular life, you’re in a strong position. Keep going. #everydaypower

You’re the director. You’re the producer. You’re the lead actress or actor. You’re the supporting cast. You’re the villain. You’re the hero. You’re even the audience. You’re all of it. How fun is that. Keep going. #everydaypower

Practice talking to yourself more and you might be stunned with the amount of actionable wisdom inside you. It’s not that we don’t have it, it’s that we don’t trust it. Tap in. Keep going. #everydaypower

The choice is yours. The choice will always be yours. Every day in every moment, we can go plus (+) or minus (-). It’s all one big game. 
And the moments and the days stack on top of each other. Every day is the main event. And it’s Your Purpose Vs. Your Fears. Some days your purpose will win. Other days your fear will win. Sometimes it will be a tie. 
It's a battle. Purpose is positive, energizing, and exciting...but it’s still a battle. Fear is natural and can keep you safe and alive...but it can also keep you in survival mode when you no longer need to be.
Every day select your purpose over your fears. Select it like you select a strong Wi-Fi signal. Select it like you would a show. Select it like you would a person to text. Select yourself. Select your purpose.
Keep going.
#everydaypower

Watch your thoughts like you would a show. Watch your responses like you watch your timeline. Find your patterns like you would a lost phone. Pay attention to how you move. You don't need to know why, you just need to know how you're moving. So...you can see if it's helping or hurting you. Then adjust your focus, like you do before every pic. COME ON, I had too!! hahaha Keep building. Keep going. #everydaypower

Don’t let your moods and fear of boring things stop you from reaching your future. 
Put yourself in the right state of mind by taking real time to imagine how it all plays out. Keep building. Keep going. #everydaypower
LFG!!! #keepgoing

The more we say tomorrow, the more we practice putting it off. The more we put it off, the more we practice tapping into the version of us that won’t make it happen. Be clear on the different versions of you. The version of you who has in the past gotten it done. And, the version of you who has not. Both versions are inside. Choose the version you want to be. Every single day. Keep going. #everydaypower #keepgoing
Give it everything you’ve got. And stop expecting the same energy from others. Keep going. #everydaypower

Every lie we tell we create more work for ourselves because now we have to remember it. That’s too much work. That’s real brain power. That’s real space in our memory, that could be used for other things. It’s like having 200 apps on your phone open at the same time. You can’t expect to have power for a long time. Be honest. Look rude sometimes. Be comfortable with being misunderstood. It will all work itself out in the long run. Keep going. #everydaypower

Sometimes you start so small you forget how you started. Remember how you started. That will keep you lean, focused, and hungry. Remember how you started. That will unlock the wisdom needed to go even further. Keep going. #everydaypower

No one wants to build discipline. But as you build it you start to develop this deep sense of confidence that you can do what others aren’t willing to do. It’s not that they can’t do it, but they choose not to because of X Y and Z. You chose to. You chose you. Respect yourself for that. Keep going. #everydaypower

We over use the word happy. Happiness can come from pleasure. But then that same pleasure can make us fat, lazy and cause problems down the line in a wide range of areas. I think what we’re really after is excitement. I think what we’re really after is the movement towards whatever it is we find important. That excitement comes from meaning. That excitement comes from purpose. That excitement makes life the best possible adventure. Keep going. #everydaypower
Be able to see what you have. It might be more than you initially think. Keep going. #everydaypower

You have millions on millions on billions of years worth of information in every cell in your body. The problem is you don’t trust yourself enough. For many reasons. Take a moment and reflect upon all the ancestors you never think of, have never met, but have played a role in contributing strengths, wisdom and knowledge into your whole entire being. How do you feel after you think about that? You never met or maybe even think about them…but you wouldn’t be here without them…and their collective life experience is all up inside of you. Your past has your back. The whole entire past has your back. Keep going. #everydaypower

You’re directly related to a level of strength, power and perseverance that’s literally hard to imagine. Take a moment and think about all the craziness that’s going on in the world right now. And multiply that times the thousands on thousands of years that we’ve been here. Then think about all the strength it takes to persevere through ALL of it. That’s where you come from. Nothing petty can stop you. Keep going. #everydaypower
More Life to everyone in 2024! Lets go! Much love! #everydaypower #keepgoing
Pay attention to what you’re paying attention to. Is it holding you back, keeping you stuck or pulling you forward. Paying attention has the best return on investment. Keep going. #everydaypower

Zoom out! Reflect! Take a moment to remember how the most helpful life lessons always came after a storm. The storms never ever come in vain. The storms always bring a level of awareness, knowledge and discipline that makes the level up truly possible. Keep going. #everydaypower

Sooner or later, you’re going to have to bet on yourself. Pay attention to your strengths. Pay attention to the needs in your industry. Pay attention to the rules of whatever industry you’re in. You’re 10-20 times smarter than you think. But that intelligence only comes to the surface when it has to. Keep going. #everydaypower
Don’t convince, just live your life with conviction. The example you set is your most powerful message. Keep going. #everydaypower

Every challenge you have is targeting a specific part of you. Every part that gets targeted, can be developed. When you add that all up, you meet a version of you that’s stronger, smarter, wiser, more creative, more disciplined, more patient and more empathetic. Which are all major traits for living a great life. Keep going. #everydaypower

You’re not lost, you just have a destination in your GPS that’s based on someone or something else. You’re not lost, you just forgot that the whispering voice inside you exists, and is the most important and honest voice in your life. You’re not lost, you’re just very very early in the process of trusting yourself. Keep going. #everydaypower

What you deeply desire, is part of the real you. Not all, but most of the things you fear, you learned how to do that. Your essence wants to move freely and lightly through this life experience. Your fears keep you trapped and heavy. The door is wide open, and the weighted vest can be taken off. Keep going. #everydaypower
Feel yourself bringing it to life. Elevate your vibration in a very real way. Keep going. #everydaypower
